<h3><a id="cert_generation"></a> Q: What tools can I use to generate certs for use with Direct?</h3>

<p>A: The only tool we know of that can generate certs meeting the requirements of Direct is the cert tool
that is included as part of the Direct Reference Implementation. The Java keytool is reported to be inadequate
and we cannot find any documentation to guide us on the use of openssl. The only relevant online documentation
we have found is:</p>

<p><a href="http://www.mail-archive.com/openssl-users@openssl.org/msg19407.html">http://www.mail-archive.com/openssl-users@openssl.org/msg19407.html</a>
<br /> and <br />
<a href="http://wiki.directproject.org/Misc+Certificate+Notes">http://wiki.directproject.org/Misc+Certificate+Notes</a></p>

